Create an object of class "rankings" from a dataframe or matrix

to_rankings(data = NULL, items = NULL, rankings = NULL,
  type = NULL, ...)

Arguments

data

a data frame with columns specified by items and rankings. Data can be in both wide and long format. An id is required if long format.
items

a data frame or vector representing the item names
rankings

a data frame or vector representing the rankings
type

optional, the type of data input, 'rank' is set by default
...

other arguments passed to methods

Value

a "rankings" object, which is a matrix of dense rankings

rankings
